<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>CVS Health (CVS)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of CVS Health Corporation — using disclosed assumptions and yielding one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Shares Out (M)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(cashAndInvestments / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Cash & Inv.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(totalDebt / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Total Debt</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — focusing strictly on the cash flow the business generates. No multiples, no comparables.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>CVS generated <strong>${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1)} billion</strong> in free cash flow. This is the real cash the business produces after paying for necessary capital expenditures. We use this as our base for projection.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This assumes modest but steady performance as the integrated healthcare model matures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> — roughly in line with long-term inflation and GDP growth. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. This represents our required rate of return, incorporating the current 10-Year Treasury rate of {riskFreeRate}% plus an equity risk premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>We add cash and subtract total debt from the present value of cash flows to find Equity Value. Finally, we divide by the {sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()} million shares outstanding.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF relies on judgment. We've made three core assumptions that dictate the final value.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A conservative estimate for CVS. Despite its massive scale and diverse operations (Aetna, Caremark, Pharmacy), healthcare margins are under pressure. A 4% growth rate assumes they successfully navigate Medicare Advantage headwinds while capitalizing on their integrated care model.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        The required return. With the 10-Year Treasury at {riskFreeRate}%, a 9% discount rate implies an equity risk premium suitable for a mature, heavily regulated, but stable healthcare conglomerate like CVS.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        2% represents steady-state growth roughly mirroring long-term U.m. economic growth and inflation. We do not assume CVS will outpace general economic growth in perpetuity.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base</td>
          <td>${fcfBase.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
